==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castigate
<hw>Cas"ti*gate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Castigated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Castigating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>castigatus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>castigare</ets> to correct, punish; <ets>castus</ets> pure,
chaste + <ets>agere</ets> to move, drive. See <er>Caste</er>, and cf.
<er>Chasten</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To punish by stripes; to
chastise by blows; to chasten; also, to chastise verbally; to reprove;
to criticise severely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To emend; to correct.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castigation</ent>⟦br⟧
